data: First target of the operation due to its commanding position over the road to Jerusalem. Taken on night of 3rd but the attackers retreated the next day. They briefly held the position on 8th and finally took complete control on 9th. All buildings including the mosque were demolished.

Inhabitants ordered to leave and the village completely levelled. Palestinian irregulars launched several counter attacks and on 9th April the British army ordered the Jewish forces out because of the threat to British supply routes.
The attackers were ordered to leave by the British army. Jewish forces bulldozed all the village buildings on 20th April.
Around a sixth of inhabitants killed after village taken.

Changed hands several times over following months, finally coming under Israeli control in July.

May have been taken in subsequent operations at the end of April.
